text: Lauren Plum (born September 17, 1992) is an American volleyball player. She played at the 2011 FIVB Women’s Junior World Championship. She played for University of Oregon's women's volleyball team, ASPTT Mulhouse, Rote Raben Vilsbiburg, VfB 91 Suhl, and Vandœuvre Nancy Volley-Ball. == References == Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:American volleyball players
